[SHORT DESC]
User is made invulnerable for one turn, then hits the next turn.

[LONG DESC]
<p>User is made invulnerable for one turn, then hits the next turn. Sky Uppercut and Thunder have regular accuracy and Base Power against a Pokémon in the middle of Fly. The Base Power of Gust and Twister doubles against a Pokémon in the charge up stage of Fly. If the user takes damage from sandstorm and hail normally, it will continue to do so on the charge turn.
</p>

<p><strong>Overworld effect:</strong> Transports the trainer to any PokeCenter he/she has previously visited, or their house in the case of Flying to his/her home town. Fly cannot be used in caves or buildings.</p>
<h2>Related Moves</h2>
<p><a href="/dp/moves/bounce">Bounce</a> is a weaker, less accurate equivalent.</p>